  <td width="82"><strong>POSITION:</strong></td>
  <td width="364" style="font-size:1.2em; font-weight:bold">Early Childhood Assistive Technology Specialist</td></tr>
<tr>
  <td><strong>SUPERVISOR:</strong></td><td>Bridget Gilormini, Director of PACER Simon Technology Center</td></tr>
<tr>
  <td><strong>STATUS:</strong></td><td>Full time, salaried monthly, exempt status</td></tr>
</table>
<p>The PACER Simon Technology  Center offers information, referral, and professional training on assistive  technology topics.&nbsp; Assistive technology  is used to help individuals with disabilities to reach their full potential. </p>
<h2><strong>Specific Duties and  Responsibilities:</strong></h2>
<ul>
  <li>Assist in training of professionals and parents about assistive technology use at home, in early childhood programs and classrooms.</li>
  <li>Provide technical assistance related to computers and assistive technology by phone, email, and in person to project participants.</li>
  <li>Keep current on state-of-the-art technology tools for meeting the needs of young children with disabilities.</li>
  <li>Be a technology resource for parents and professionals.</li>
  <li>Assist with project data collection and evaluation.</li>
  <li>Read and review technology articles and resources and write articles for PACER publications.</li>
  <li>Present workshops and in-services for parents and professionals on assistive technology.</li>
  <li>Serve as an advocate for the technology needs of children with disabilities.</li>
  <li>Prepare and conduct individual consultations for families of children with disabilities.</li>
  <li>Other tasks as needed.</li>
</ul>
<h2><strong>Requirements</strong></h2>
<ul>
          <li>Early Childhood Special Educators, Occupational Therapists/Certified Occupational Therapy Assistants, Physical Therapists/Physical Therapy Assistants, or Speech Therapy/Speech Therapy Assistants are encouraged to apply </li>
          <li>Knowledge of or willingness to learn about Assistive Technology</li>
          <li>Technical expertise using the Macintosh and/or PC computers and educational software </li>
          <li>Technical expertise using mobile technology including the iOS/Android operating system</li>
          <li>Familiarity with educational issues for young children with disabilities </li>
          <li>Good teaching, training, and presentation skills </li>
          <li>Sensitivity to and knowledge of cultural competence related to a variety of cultures </li>
          <li>Excellent interpersonal skills and ability to work in teams </li>
          <li>Excellent written and verbal communication skills</li>
          <li>Excellent organizational skills with the ability to prioritize tasks and give attention to detail</li>
          <li>Ability to work flexible hours; some overnight travel may be required</li>
</ul>

<p>Parents of children and young adults with disabilities are encouraged to apply.  Salary will be based on  experience and qualifications. Position is open until filled.</p>
